---
description: UI design language rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow the existing SASV Workspace design language.

General UI rules:

- Use existing card, toolbar, filter, table, modal, tab, toast, and badge styles.
- Do not introduce a new visual language.
- Reuse shared CSS classes before creating new CSS.
- Keep layouts mobile-friendly and desktop-friendly.
- Prefer two-line filter layouts where existing modules use them.
- Keep Clear actions as text links where existing modules do so.
- Maintain dark-theme compatibility.
- Do not use pure black backgrounds unless already used by the project.
- Keep table cards visually consistent with established modules.
